  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "PD E2E tests have very aggressive clean up routine that does not wait for volumes to safely detached. After the test completes, the test cleanup routine unilaterally detaches the PD (instead of waiting for k8s to do it cleanly). Although this does not cause the test to fail, it results in errors in the kernel logs:\n\n```\n[ 3990.304541] end_request: I/O error, dev sdc, sector 0\n[ 3990.335060] sd 0:0:4:0: [sdc] Synchronizing SCSI cache\n[ 3990.342185] sd 0:0:4:0: [sdc]  \n[ 3990.346675] Result: hostbyte=DID_BAD_TARGET driverbyte=DRIVER_OK\n...\n[ 4019.200889] Buffer I/O error on device sdc, logical block 1081344\n[ 4019.207365] lost page write due to I/O error on sdc\n[ 4019.212389] JBD2: Error -5 detected when updating journal superblock for sdc-8.\n[ 4019.219852] Aborting journal on device sdc-8.\n[ 4019.224593] Buffer I/O error on device sdc, logical block 1081344\n[ 4019.231940] lost page write due to I/O error on sdc\n[ 4019.237367] JBD2: Error -5 detected when updating journal superblock for sdc-8.\n```\n\nWe should modify these tests to wait for k8s to safely detach the disk.\n",
